						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 845</hi> (= A.D. 923-24) with no further details. It seems to refer itself to the reign of a <hi rend="bold">Noḻamba-Pallava chief</hi> (name lost) and mentions the death of <hi rend="bold">Eḍeyamma,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Haritta,</hi> after a brave fight against <hi rend="bold">Sēvuṇa's</hi> army, so as to bring tears to all. Rācha's son Aṇuga set up the stone.</p>						

						<p>First Section.</p>						

						</summary>
